<font color="#FF0000">NUMBERS, NUMBERS WAS THE GAME</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 17 18:48:11 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John<br>
It had nothing to do with poor folks or rich folks, it all had to do with how slick the NAVY, ARMY, AIR FORCE or Marine Recruiter was. It had to do with what type of promotion the service agencies were offering to the top recruiter for the week.  <br>
Look at the stats, each time a week end pass was offered or a top duty assignement was offered more unsuspecting high school students were promised a rose Garden by their local recruiter if they would just sign, on the bottom line. <br>
Yep! that's what it really was all about.
<p><code>-- Still waiting to collect, what my recruiter promised  (Sparrowhawk) </code><p>


